              <title>Session: Context and Collaborative Learning Design</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/2503</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/2503</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>This session will describe the collaborative team approach and provide some examples of collaborative learning design models used at <a href="http://www.bcit.ca/">British Columbia Institute of Technology</a>. BCIT is characterized by a considerable range of programs and students, which requires careful consideration of the teaching and learning context and the various stakeholders &ndash; professional governing bodies, industry, subject matter experts, and program requirements &ndash; in the development of learning and teaching materials. As a result, the e-learning continuum is quite varied at BCIT and presents both challenge and opportunities.</p>]]></description>
